---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="jystmik3 | Michael Lilley"
  description="What Google knows about Michael Lilley. What it doesn't. A personal page about the gap.">

  <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">jystmik3</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 font-mono">/dʒɪst·maɪk/ — noun. A handle. A void. A man the algorithm can't summarize.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">What Google Knows</h2>
        
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          If you search for me, the algorithm returns a tidy package. Army veteran. FAA Part 107 certified. ITC Level I Thermographer. Founder of Wet Dog Drones Inc., incorporated in Colorado, September 2025. Twelve years in the drone space. Five commercially. Over a thousand flights. A quarter-million dollars in documented client savings across three case studies.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          It knows about the DJI Mavic 3 E with RTK. The Trimble DA2. The 24–48 hour data turnaround. The bi-weekly progress flights. The case study where pre-construction baseline documentation split a $40,000 change order in half. The one where interior documentation proved a building was empty when copper went missing, saving $400,000.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          It knows I'm based in Deer Trail, Colorado. It knows my email. It knows I've been a member of The Droning Company since September 2023. It has my LinkedIn photo.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-8 rounded-lg my-10">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-800">Your Internet Summary, per Google</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>Army veteran</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">10+ years in drone space</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>FAA Part 107</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">ITC Level I Thermographer</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>Wet Dog Drones Inc.</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">Founded Sept 2025, CO</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>$440K+ saved</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">Across documented projects</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>1,000+ flights</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">24–48 hr turnaround</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <div><strong>Deer Trail, CO</strong><br/><span class="text-slate-500">Front Range & Eastern Plains</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">What Google Doesn't Know</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          Try searching "jystmik3." Go ahead. I'll wait.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          Nothing. Zero results. A complete vacuum. The search engine that indexes the planet returns an empty page for the name I've used across platforms for years. That's not an accident — that's by design. Some things you keep off the public record because not everything needs to be legible to an algorithm.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          The internet knows the business owner. It knows the certifications and the case studies. It doesn't know the 1 AM emails. The $7,000 personal loan. The three years of grinding before consistent revenue. It doesn't know the dog who comes to work and finds every mud puddle on site — which is how the company got its name. It doesn't know why someone would build autonomous AI agents at 2 AM after a full day on a construction site.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="bg-slate-100 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-8 text-xl italic">
          "The metadata doesn't lie. That's the only thing that matters when a $400,000 change order is on the line."
        </blockquote>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          That's the line from the website. It's true. But the metadata also doesn't tell you the full story. It never does. A search result is a silhouette, not a portrait.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">About the Handle</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          "jystmik3" is deliberate. It's not a brand. It's not SEO-optimized. It's a name that doesn't resolve neatly into a LinkedIn profile or a Google Knowledge Panel. It's a reminder that some parts of your identity should stay illegible to the machine — not out of paranoia, but out of choice.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          The internet will tell you I fly drones over construction sites in Colorado. It won't tell you I build AI agents that operate autonomously. It won't tell you about the late-night tinkering, the failed projects, the things I've built and torn down and built again. It won't tell you about the person behind the Part 107 certificate.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-300 p-8 rounded-lg my-10 font-mono text-sm">
          <p class="mb-2"><span class="text-green-400">$</span> web_search "jystmik3"</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-slate-500"> Searching Brave, Exa, DuckDuckGo...</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-red-400"> 0 results found.</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-slate-500"> Searching Reddit, GitHub, LinkedIn...</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-yellow-400"> GitHub: Jystmik3 (5 public repos, 0 followers, 0 following)</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-yellow-400"> Reddit: no results.</p>
          <p class="mb-2 text-slate-500"> Searching news archives...</p>
          <p class="text-red-400"> 0 results found.</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-green-400">$ _</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Point</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          This page exists because someone asked an AI to "Google me" and build whatever it found. The AI found the business. The certifications. The case studies. It found a tidy narrative about a drone pilot in Colorado. And it found nothing about jystmik3.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          That gap — between what the internet knows and what it doesn't — is the most honest thing about me online. The algorithm can summarize my work. It can't summarize me.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-4">
          And that's exactly how I want it.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Actual Facts (for the record)</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-slate-600">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">01</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">Location</strong><br/>
            Deer Trail, Colorado. Eastern Plains.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">02</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">Company</strong><br/>
            Wet Dog Drones Inc. Construction drone services.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">03</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">Certification</strong><br/>
            FAA Part 107. ITC Level I sUAS Thermographer.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">04</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">Background</strong><br/>
            U.S. Army veteran. 12 years in drone space.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">05</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">GitHub</strong><br/>
            <a href="https://github.com/Jystmik3" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">github.com/Jystmik3</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-slate-400 font-mono text-sm mt-0.5">06</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-800">Contact</strong><br/>
            <a href="mailto:michael@wetdogdrones.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">michael@wetdogdrones.com</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-slate-900 text-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-mono mb-2">This page was generated by an autonomous AI agent on May 11, 2026.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-mono mb-2">Search sources: Brave, Exa, public web crawl.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-mono">No vault. No local data. Just what the internet knows.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
